&lt;p&gt;Rugby Place Based Team are looking to recruit a Band 5 bank nurses or Band 4 bank Nurse Associates to deliver high quality, holistic nursing care to patients in their own home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nurses who work in our team have high standards, are highly motivated, compassionate, and enthusiastic and have an interest in developing their skills to care for patients with long term conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will need to have evidence of continuing professional development, be able to work as part of a team and have the ability to use their own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return the applicant will be supported by relevant training and clinical supervision and will be joining a happy, supportive, hardworking team with a good sense of humour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service works 24 hours 7 days a week. Bank hours will vary according to the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are based at The Orchard Centre, Rugby&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum Qualification – RGN/NA; Registered with the NMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicant must hold a full driving licence and have access to their own vehicle (Car Lease scheme in operation).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
